# Frontend Design and Development Rules

When creating or modifying any frontend files, you must adhere to the following UI/UX and design guidelines.

## 1. Color Palette

Use the following color variables for all UI elements. Do not use hardcoded hex codes.

| Role          | Color Name      | Hex Code    |
| :------------ | :-------------- | :---------- |
| **Primary**   | School Blue     | `#005A9C`   |
| **Secondary** | Success Green   | `#28A745`   |
| **Accent**    | Notice Yellow   | `#FFC107`   |
| **Text**      | Dark Charcoal   | `#333333`   |
| **Background**| Light Gray      | `#F8F9FA`   |
| **Border**    | Subtle Gray     | `#DEE2E6`   |

## 2. Typography (Mandatory Bengali Fonts)

The application must support both Bengali and English. For Bengali text, you must use the specified fonts from the CDN.

*   **Primary Font:** `Kalpurush` must be the default font for the `body`.
    ```css
    body {
      font-family: 'Kalpurush', Arial, sans-serif !important;
    }
    ```
*   **Embedding in HTML:** Ensure the font's CSS file is linked in the `<head>` of the main HTML document.
    ```html
    <link href="https://cdn.msar.me/fonts/kalpurush/font.css" rel="stylesheet">
    ```

*   **Other Fonts:** `Mukti`, `SiyamRupali`, and `SolaimanLipi` can be used for specific elements by applying dedicated classes (e.g., `.font-mukti`). Refer to `AGENTS.md` for their CDN links.

## 3. Accessibility

*   Use semantic HTML5 tags (`<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, etc.).
*   Ensure all images have descriptive `alt` attributes.
*   Ensure all form inputs have associated `<label>` tags.